title: Ed Schultz Show with Mike Papantonio - October 25 2013
description:
October 25, 2013
Ed Schultz Show

Mike Papantonio from the Ring of Fire Radio Show fills in for Big Eddie!

Newspaper publisher Rick Outzen will be here to run down the news of the day.
 
Journalist and author David Sirota will discuss the latest developments in the plot to steal public employee pensions.
 
Richard Eskow from the Campaign for AmericaÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s Future will tell us why the Democrats need to go on the offensive against the GOP war on government.
 
And investigative journalist Lee Fang from The Nation will explain the hidden dangers in the Supreme CourtÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s McCutcheon case.

America's top diplomat warned on Thursday that the United States could suffer more lasting damage to its influence abroad if the next round of budget talks in a few months lead to another breakdown. We'll give you the details.

A new round of U.S. budget negotiations starting next week should focus more narrowly on replacing automatic spending cuts rather than an elusive "grand bargain," House Budget Committee Chairman Paul Ryan said on Thursday. We'll bring you the latest.

The Obama administration launched its troubled healthcare insurance website after only a minimum of crucial system-wide testing, despite contractors warning officials repeatedly about performance risks, a congressional panel heard on Thursday. We'll talk about it.
